README: epackage.el for Emacs
-----------------------------

Description

        An Emacs extension for Distributed Emacs Lisp Package System
        (DELPS). With it, you can install Emacs extensions that have
        been put available as git DVCS repositories. This format is
        called "epackage".

Important files

        COPYING*        GPL-2+ Source. Docs are dual GPL-2+/GFDL
        INSTALL         Install instructions
        ChangeLog       Project change records

Project details

        Homepage        http://freshmeat.net/projects/emacs-epackage
        Wiki            http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/DELPS
        Manual          http://www.nongnu.org/emacs-epackage/manual
        Bugs            See freshmeat page
        Source code     See freshmeat page

        Depends
        - Emacs 22.1+ (released 2007).
        - Git[1], any version.
        - Depends only on standard Emacs. Does not use external or
          "cl" libraries.

	Depends (optional)
        - Perl, and utilities: ripdoc[2] and t2html[3].
          Use in Makefile's "make doc" command to generate HTML
          documentation.
        - OpenSSH client, any version. For package maintainers that
	  push packages to remote git:// repositories.

References

        [1] Git Distributed Version Control System (DVCS).
            http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git_(software)

        [2] Extract documentation that follows Technical Text Format guidelines
            http://freshmeat.net/projects/perl-ripdoc

        [3] Convert Technical Text Format into HTML
            http://freshmeat.net/projects/perl-text2html

